At this juncture..it seems like a good idea to come up with a &quot;No Sweat&quot; lodge.  Brothers can come here to divest themselves of problems .. and their brothers can convince them...&quot;No Sweat!&quot;  Not to play down, ignore or discredit the presented problem..but to convey the true meaning of &quot;No Sweat.&quot;<br>
Ancient warriors would present themselves before someone's lodge and give away everything they owned.. including weapons, horses, food and even the clothes on their back.  It was not an act of generosity, but a statement..&quot;If I lose everything.. still I can start over and rise to greatness again!&quot;  It was a tangible gesture that strength and goodness dwell in me and not my material things... I am made of &quot;good&quot; stuff! ...I own the Earth!<br>
The &quot;No Sweat&quot; lodge is a good place to come and let your brothers give you strength.. it is a good place to laugh at your own weakness in the company of men who have cried before you!<br>
Regardless of the wounds of circumstance and the taunts of the manitous...here each will remain, &quot;Wica'sa Okinihan,&quot; an honorable and respected brother..Forever!<br>
This lodge faces East to remind us of the need for new beginnings as we listen to the threats of the Thunder Beings!  Here we will become wanagi yuha, spirit owners.. and the Creator will enter and give the gift of his voice.  We will learn that..Mita wasicun he omakiyake, the familiar voice that resides within me is the voice of my Father.. and he is wiser than I!<br><br>
I am Tatekohomi Wambli, Whirlwind Eagle!  Maka kin le mitawaka, I own the Earth!  <br>
Hiye pila maya, Wankantanka!  Thank you, Great Holy Mystery!<br><br>
 
